Method.СообщитьПользователю.Description=Generates and outputs a message that can be associated with a form\ncontrol.
Method.СообщитьПользователю.Example.Description=1. To output a message at a managed form field associated with an object attribute\:\nCommonClientServer.MessageToUser(\nNStr("en \= 'Error message.'"), ,\n"FieldInFormAttributeObject",\n"Object");\nAlternative usage in an object form\:\nCommonClientServer.MessageToUser(\nNStr("en \= 'Error message.'"), ,\n"Object.FieldInFormAttributeObject");\n2. To output a message next to a managed form field associated with a form attribute\:\nCommonClientServer.MessageToUser(\nNStr("en \= 'Error message.'"), ,\n"FormAttributeName");\n3. To output a message associated with an infobase object\:\nCommonClientServer.MessageToUser(\nNStr("en \= 'Error message.'"), InfobaseObject, "Responsible",,Cancel);\n4. To output a message by reference to an infobase object\:\nCommonClientServer.MessageToUser(\nNStr("en \= 'Error message.'"), Reference, , , Cancel);\nIncorrect usage cases\:\n1. Passing the DataKey and DataPath parameters at the same time.\n2. Passing a value of a type other than allowed in the DataKey parameter.\n3. Setting a reference without setting a field (and/or path to data).\n@skip-check method-too-many-params
Method.СообщитьПользователю.Name=MessageToUser
